INSERT INTO Lore(OBJECT_NAME,ITEM_TYPE,MAT_CLASS,MATERIAL,WEIGHT,ITEM_VALUE,EXTRA,CREATE_DATE,SUBMITTER)
VALUES('crown tides coral blue pearl-encrusted','WORN','natural','stone',6,'2000','Flickering images of the Crown''s storied past swim before your eyes:,The first image shows the audience hall of the Tower of the Sea. An ancient,dimernesti priest is carefully placing the Crown upon the head the majestic,matriarch who brought her brethren back together to found the ancient city,of Dimernost. The various clan leaders fill the audience hall, preparing to,swear fealty to her family.,The next image depicts a young Speaker of the Sea standing waist-deep in a,tide pool, surrounded by human ambassadors. She draws them close and utters,the words, ''adjarjiog'' (which sounds like "aqualungs" to you), and the cool,water in the pool suddenly becomes effervescent. The frightened ambassadors,look surprised as the fizzy bubbles leap down their throats, but afterwards,they descend into the ocean together.,The final image shows a mighty Speaker using the Crown of Tides to fend off,an attack from an enormous sea dragon, and somehow you divine that his name,was Brynseldimer. The last thing you glimpse is the huge dragon being slain,by the Speaker''s allies before another wave of enemies overwhelms the city.','2017-04-12 16:41:58','James');
